Installing the hMailServer Password changer Plugin
======================================

1) Start with copying the plugin to the SM plugin directory.

2) Then go to your SM config directory and run conf.pl.  Choose
   option 8 and move the plugin from the "Available Plugins" 
   category to the "Installed Plugins" category.  Save and exit.
   If you don't have perl installed, edit config.php manually.
   (search for plugin in it).
   
3) If you are using hMailServer 4.3 or later, set the hMailServer
   Administrator password in config.php in this directory.